Init Container:
----- -------
These are very common Kubernetes interview topics.
Init Container
An Init Container runs before the main application container starts.
Think of it as a setup or preparation container.
Init Container 1
      ↓
Init Container 2
      ↓
Main Container
The main container will not start until all init containers finish successfully.

---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
1.vim init-cont.yaml

apiVersion: v1
kind: Pod
metadata:
  name: init-container-demo
  namespace: test-ns
spec:
  containers:
  - name: main-app
    image: busybox
    command:
    - sh
    - -c
    - echo Main App Running; sleep 3600

  initContainers:
  - name: wait-for-mongodb
    image: busybox
    command:
    - sh
    - -c
    - |
      until nc -z mongodb 27017
      do
        echo "Waiting for MongoDB..."
        sleep 5
      done  
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Why do we need this?

Imagine:

MongoDB Pod      -> Starting
Spring Boot Pod  -> Starting

If Spring Boot starts first and tries to connect:

mongodb:27017

MongoDB may not be ready yet.

Result:

Connection Refused
Application Crash

The Init Container prevents that.

Step 1
name: wait-for-mongodb

Init Container name:

wait-for-mongodb
Step 2
image: busybox

Uses a lightweight Linux image.

BusyBox contains tools like:

sh
nc
wget
ping
sleep
Step 3
command:
- sh
- -c

Equivalent to:

sh -c "<script>"

Runs the shell script below.

Step 4
until nc -z mongodb 27017
What is nc?

nc = Netcat

Used to test network connectivity.

Example:

nc -z mongodb 27017

Meaning:

Try connecting to host:
mongodb

Port:
27017

MongoDB default port is:

27017
What does -z mean?
nc -z mongodb 27017

-z means:

Check if port is open
Don't send data

Just test connectivity.

Example

If MongoDB is running:

nc -z mongodb 27017

returns:

Success

Exit code:

0

If MongoDB is not ready:

nc -z mongodb 27017

returns:

Connection refused

Exit code:

1
Step 5
until nc -z mongodb 27017

The shell keyword:

until

means:

Keep looping UNTIL command succeeds

Equivalent logic:

While MongoDB is NOT reachable
    keep waiting
Step 6
do
  echo "Waiting for MongoDB..."
  sleep 5
done

Every 5 seconds:

Waiting for MongoDB...

is printed.

Then:

sleep 5

Waits 5 seconds.

Then checks MongoDB again.

Timeline Example
Time 0

MongoDB not ready.

nc -z mongodb 27017

fails.

Output:

Waiting for MongoDB...
Time 5 sec

Checks again.

Still fails.

Output:

Waiting for MongoDB...
Time 10 sec

Checks again.

Still fails.

Output:

Waiting for MongoDB...
Time 15 sec

MongoDB becomes ready.

nc -z mongodb 27017

succeeds.

Loop ends.

Init Container exits successfully.

Then

Kubernetes starts the main container.

Init Container Finished
          ↓
Spring Boot Starts
Visual Flow
Pod Created
      |
      v
Init Container Starts
      |
      v
Check mongodb:27017
      |
      +----Not Ready----+
      |                 |
      |                 v
      |        Sleep 5 Seconds
      |                 |
      +-----------------+
      |
      v
MongoDB Ready
      |
      v
Init Container Exits
      |
      v
Main Container Starts




