Interview Questions
What is an Init Container?

A special container that runs before the main container and must finish successfully before the application starts.

Why use Init Containers?
Wait for database
Download files
Configure environment
Database migrations
What is a Sidecar Container?

A secondary container running alongside the main container in the same Pod to provide supporting functionality such as logging, monitoring, proxying, or security.

Give real-world Sidecar examples.
Fluentd for logs
Envoy in Istio
Nginx reverse proxy
Monitoring agents
Easy way to remember
Init Container
=
Prepare the house before people enter.

Sidecar Container
=
Security guard staying with the house all day.
